		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Silly Tips on Playing your Ranger<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Jul 23rd 12:08 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=99590450999316&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=99590450999316&post=1&replyto=99590450999316"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=99590450999316></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Top Ten Ranger Rules<br><br>1) Rangers are NOT tanks.<br>2) Leave Tanking to the warriors, pallies or shadow knight.<br>3) Rangers, like monks and rouges are melee damage dealers.<br>4) Destroy your taunt button it will only get you into trouble.<br>5) Attack a mob a few seconds after the main tanks engage.<br>5) When in a grp do not snare a mob until its below half health<br>6) Always have Jolt memmed.<br>7) Use Jolt only if the tanks can not taunt the mob off you.<br>8) IF you are to low to have Jolt, turn attack off it you get to much agro.<br>9) Have a change out of weapons so that you have slower weapons available to reduce agro <br>10) Rangers are a skill class. If you know you are not a skill player pick another class that is easier to play.<br><br>Actually the suggestions I am making are just methods I have used to keep my&nbsp;&nbsp;Ranger out of trouble. Remember you sucking up damage is not a smart thing. It puts extra strain on your healer(s) and this does not help out your grp.<br><br>Get as much AC as possible, for those situations where you do get agro,  BUT if you play you Ranger smart you wont get hit much. <br><br>Remember you job in a groupr, unless your the only melee is NOT to tank. You job  its to do damage after the tank has drawn the agro. The skills you neeed to develop focus on keeping the agro off you, and then knowing what to do once that agro is on you. IF you learn these you will be a welcome addition to any group as you can do more damage than any class other than a Monk and Rouge. And on top of either of those other damage dealing classes you have some nice spells to augment your grp some of which no other class can provide.<br><br>Valdiar Silvermist 59 Outrider of Tunaree on Mith Marr</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >3 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
