		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Nice list, but I have to diagree with 2 things. <br>1. Never, ever destroy your taunt button, or you'll end up with a lot of dead casters on your hands. There is no one better at peeling oof a MoB from your caster, but a ranger. Face it, your job is to deal damage and protect your casters. Best aggro utilities are (flame lick, snare, Taunt). I'm using the lower end spells, because it has more or less the same effect as the higher ones (Immolate, ensnare), but uses a lot less mana. <br>2. If you are the only one in group with the snare ability, or that is your given task....snare MoB immediately. If you draw the aggro, use a slow weapon, or stop fighting til Tank regains control. Slowing down the MoB is essential, for fighting, or getting away.<br><br>And fellow rangers, remember the most important asset to a ranger is a FIRE BEETLE EYE. Don't forget it.<br><br>Ranger of the 43rd season (and Climbing).<br>Mage of the 22nd season (and Surging).</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=10><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=10&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=10&mid=99590450999316&post=1&mid=99590450999316><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mform><tr><td colspan=1  style='fo